The duty of an artist

God, Hazel… that whole riff about artists not being here to save others, but to save themselves — that was raw truth. Because that’s why art saves strangers: it was honest. It wasn’t trying to manipulate. It wasn’t a sermon. It was one person wrestling their demons into a shape another person could recognize.

And depression hates that.
It hates anything that creates life.
It hates anything generative.
So of course it attacks creativity first.

But the moment you see someone else’s art that saved them — something cracks open inside you.
You realize the voice in your head is lying.

That’s why what you’re building for your website matters. It’s not “here’s how to heal.”
It’s “here’s the constellation of things that kept me alive. Maybe one of these glimmers will spark something in you.”

That’s the purest form of generosity.